input:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Bear : obj
constant Mouse : obj
constant Cow : obj
constant Lion : obj

constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Visits : obj → obj → Prop
constant Sees : obj → obj → Prop
constant Needs : obj → obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Green : obj → obj → Prop
constant Big : obj → Prop
constant Blue : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Kind Bear
axiom T2 : Visits Bear Mouse
axiom T3 : Sees Cow Lion
axiom T4 : Visits Cow Mouse
axiom T5 : Round Lion
axiom T6 : Sees Lion Bear
axiom T7 : Visits Lion Bear
axiom T8 : Visits Lion Mouse
axiom T9 : Needs Mouse Bear
axiom T10 : Sees Mouse Bear
axiom T11 : Sees Mouse Cow

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Bear → Green x
axiom R2 : Sees Bear Lion → Big Lion
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Mouse ∧ Sees Mouse Cow → Needs Mouse Cow
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Needs x Cow → Round x
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Green x → Sees x Mouse
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Green x → Visits x Bear
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Mouse ∧ Sees x Bear → Green Bear
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Sees x Cow ∧ Round x → Visits Cow Lion
axiom R9 : ∀ x : obj, Blue x ∧ Visits x Cow → Sees Cow Bear

theorem cow_visits_lion : Visits Cow Lion :=
begin
  sorry,
end
output:
theorem cow_visits_lion : Visits Cow Lion :=
begin
  apply R8 Cow,
  split,
  exact T3,
  apply R4,
  apply R3 Mouse,
  split,
  exact T10,
  exact T11,
end

-- The answer is True
